   1:Src/main.c    **** /**
   2:Src/main.c    ****  * main.c — WSN position receive test (no drive)
   3:Src/main.c    ****  *
   4:Src/main.c    ****  * The STM32 sits stationary, connected to the robot_esp via USART1.
   5:Src/main.c    ****  * It continuously sends temperature readings to the ESP (which forwards them
   6:Src/main.c    ****  * over Zigbee to the coordinator) and prints every position frame it receives
   7:Src/main.c    ****  * from the ESP to the ST-Link VCP on USART2 so it can be read in a terminal.
   8:Src/main.c    ****  *
   9:Src/main.c    ****  * Use this to verify the full chain:
  10:Src/main.c    ****  *   LM34 → USART1 → robot_esp → Zigbee → coordinator  (temperature path)
  11:Src/main.c    ****  *   anchors → Zigbee → robot_esp → trilateration → USART1 → here  (position path)
  12:Src/main.c    ****  *
  13:Src/main.c    ****  * Peripherals:
  14:Src/main.c    ****  *   USART2  PA2/PA3  115200 8N1  ST-Link VCP debug output      (uart.c)
  15:Src/main.c    ****  *   USART1  PA9/PA10 115200 8N1  ESP32-C6 link                  (uart1.c)
  16:Src/main.c    ****  *   ADC1    PA0      LM34 VOUT                                   (lm34.c)
  17:Src/main.c    ****  *   TIM6             µs/ms delays                                (clock.c)
  18:Src/main.c    ****  *
  19:Src/main.c    ****  * Wiring (STM32 ↔ ESP32-C6):
  20:Src/main.c    ****  *   STM32 PA9  (USART1_TX)  →  ESP32-C6 GPIO11 (RX)
  21:Src/main.c    ****  *   STM32 PA10 (USART1_RX)  ←  ESP32-C6 GPIO10 (TX)
  22:Src/main.c    ****  *   STM32 GND               —  ESP32-C6 GND
  23:Src/main.c    ****  */
  24:Src/main.c    **** 
  25:Src/main.c    **** #include <string.h>
  26:Src/main.c    **** #include "stm32l452xx.h"
  27:Src/main.c    **** #include "clock.h"
  28:Src/main.c    **** #include "lm34.h"
  29:Src/main.c    **** #include "uart.h"
  30:Src/main.c    **** #include "uart1.h"
